Prostate cancer can be diagnosed by detecting an elevated PSA (prostate specific antigen) in the blood or by feeling an abnormal prostate gland by rectal exam. The American Cancer Society recommends discussing PSA blood testing with your physician for all men greater than age 50. However, these tests are not perfect, since men without prostate cancer can have an abnormal PSA or an enlarged prostate.
